<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rage Against the Machine Honored  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Socially conscious rockers Rage Against the
Machine took home five awards at the California Music Awards.
</P>
<P>
   Led by frontman Zack de la Rocha, the Los Angeles band won the
outstanding hard rock/heavy metal album award for ''The Battle of
Los Angeles.''
</P>
<P>
   They also won outstanding group, artist of the year, and the
Arthur M. Sohcot Award for Public Excellence. Band member Tom
Morello took home the outstanding guitarist award.
</P>
<P>
   Grammy award-winner Carlos Santana won the outstanding album
award for ''Supernatural.'' His song ''Smooth,'' featuring singer
Rob Thomas of Matchbox 20, won for outstanding single.
</P>
<P>
   The awards had been known as the Bay Area Music Awards, or
Bammies, but now include musical acts from across the state.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
