<HEADLINE> Film Double Killed in Auto Accident  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   QUITO, Ecuador (AP) -- A movie double for Russell Crowe, who is
filming ''Proof of Life'' in Ecuador, was killed Sunday when a
pickup truck carrying members of the production went off a mountain
road and tumbled some 450 feet into a gorge, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Hollywood stuntman Willie Garner, whose age and hometown were
not released, died of apparent multiple fractures and massive
trauma in the accident, which occurred 50 miles west of the
capital, Quito, said police spokesman Patricio Quimzo.
</P>
<P>
   Five members of the production crew also were injured.
</P>
<P>
   ''They were on their way to film a scene on an abandoned road
and the vehicle in which they were riding crashed and fell into a
ravine,'' Quimzo told The Associated Press.
</P>
<P>
   None of the film's principal actors -- Crowe, Meg Ryan, David
Morse and David Caruso -- were riding in the truck.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities were investigating the cause of the accident.
</P>
<P>
   Five Ecuadorean extras and production technicians were being
treated in a hospital in Quito, police said. Their conditions were
not immediately available.
</P>
<P>
   Castle Rock Entertainment started location filming of ''Proof of
Life,'' a romantic drama, last month.
</P>
<P>
   The film tells the story of Alicia (Ryan), who hires a
professional negotiator (Crowe) to obtain the release of her
engineer husband (Morse), who has been kidnapped by anti-government
guerrillas.
</P>
</TEXT>
